                <div class="abstract__title abstract__title--noborder">Abstract</div>
                <div class="abstract__content">
                    <input id="summary-text-field" type="hidden" value="RegenBase is a knowledge base of spinal cord injury biology that integrates statements from published research with experimental data profiling the effects of small molecules on kinase activity and neurite growth. In this presentation, I describe recent work to extend RegenBase by incorporating large-scale gene expression data to enable querying for genes whose expression changes significantly following nerve injury. Our Linked Data representation of gene expression data allows querying based on gene identity, direction of change in gene expression, statistical significance of measured gene expression, and the time point of any observed gene expression value with respect to time of injury. Our representation enables automatic integration with existing Bio2RDF datasets, to support querying for genes based on homology and conserved domains of their protein products. We describe the gene expression data representation and content, gene expression-related queries to RegenBase and their results. The addition of gene expression data to RegenBase allows research to ask questions about the role of genes and gene expression in modulating response to nerve injury." />
                </div>
            </div>



